1
00:00:03,922 --> 00:00:06,174
Ross kissed me.

2
00:00:06,424 --> 00:00:08,676
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Oh, my God!

3
00:00:08,927 --> 00:00:10,303
It was unbelievable!

4
00:00:10,553 --> 00:00:13,556
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Oh, my God!

5
00:00:13,806 --> 00:00:15,266
Let's hear everything.

6
00:00:15,517 --> 00:00:18,228
Monica, get the wine
and unplug the phone.

7
00:00:18,478 --> 00:00:21,981
Rachel, does this end well
or do we need to get tissues?

8
00:00:22,232 --> 00:00:25,068
It ended very well.

9
00:00:25,318 --> 00:00:28,196
Do not start without me!
Do not start without me!

10
00:00:28,446 --> 00:00:31,032
Okay. All right.
Let's hear about the kiss.

11
00:00:31,282 --> 00:00:33,660
Was it a soft brush
against your lips...

12
00:00:33,910 --> 00:00:37,747
...or was it a "I gotta have you now"
kind of thing?

13
00:00:37,997 --> 00:00:42,085
Well, at first it was really intense,
you know? And then...

14
00:00:42,335 --> 00:00:45,672
Oh, God. And then we just
sort of sunk into it.

15
00:00:45,922 --> 00:00:49,509
So was he holding you?
Or were his hands on your back?

16
00:00:49,759 --> 00:00:53,221
No, actually, first
they started out on my waist...

17
00:00:53,471 --> 00:00:57,559
...and then they slid up
and were in my hair.

18
00:00:59,352 --> 00:01:00,353
And...

19
00:01:00,603 --> 00:01:01,855
...then I kissed her.

20
00:01:02,105 --> 00:01:02,939
Tongue?

21
00:01:03,189 --> 00:01:06,484
- Yeah.
- Cool.

22
00:01:06,484 --> 00:01:09,654
The One With the List

23
00:01:51,904 --> 00:01:54,031
All right, check out this bad boy!

24
00:01:54,281 --> 00:01:57,576
Twelve megabytes of RAM,
500-megabyte hard drive...

25
00:01:57,827 --> 00:01:59,578
...built-in spreadsheet capabilities...

26
00:01:59,829 --> 00:02:03,749
...and a modem that transmits
at over 28,000 BPS.

27
00:02:03,999 --> 00:02:06,335
What will you use it for?

28
00:02:06,585 --> 00:02:09,922
Games and stuff.

29
00:02:10,256 --> 00:02:12,883
There are no jobs.
There are no jobs for me.

30
00:02:13,134 --> 00:02:15,427
Oh, wait, here's one.

31
00:02:15,678 --> 00:02:19,807
- Would you be willing to cook naked?
- There's an ad for a naked chef?

32
00:02:20,057 --> 00:02:24,770
No, but if you'll cook naked, then
you might be willing to dance naked.

33
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:27,982
And then...

34
00:02:30,151 --> 00:02:33,863
So how'd you make out last night?

35
00:02:36,198 --> 00:02:38,659
That is funny.
That is painfully funny.

36
00:02:38,909 --> 00:02:40,286
No, wait, wait.

37
00:02:40,536 --> 00:02:42,830
Yeah, that's just painful.

38
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:46,167
Wait a minute.
I thought last night was great.

39
00:02:46,417 --> 00:02:48,252
Yeah, it was.
But I get home...

40
00:02:48,502 --> 00:02:51,714
...and I see Julie's saline solution
on my night table...

41
00:02:51,964 --> 00:02:54,300
...and I think,
"My God! What am I doing?"

42
00:02:54,550 --> 00:02:57,386
Here I am with Julie,
this incredible, great woman...

43
00:02:57,636 --> 00:03:00,347
...who I care about
and who cares about me...

44
00:03:00,598 --> 00:03:02,975
...and I'm just
throwing all that away?

45
00:03:03,225 --> 00:03:06,479
You got all that
from saline solution?

46
00:03:06,886 --> 00:03:10,947
I'm the same way. Show me a bottle
of Visine and I am like, "Who am I?"

47
00:03:13,229 --> 00:03:16,524
Wait. We're talking about Rachel.
You and Rachel.

48
00:03:16,774 --> 00:03:19,694
I've been dreaming about
me and Rachel for 10 years.

49
00:03:19,944 --> 00:03:21,654
But now I'm with Julie.

50
00:03:21,904 --> 00:03:24,740
So it's like, me and Julie,
me and Rachel.

51
00:03:24,991 --> 00:03:27,451
Me and Julie, me and Rach...

52
00:03:27,702 --> 00:03:29,870
Rachel! Rachel.

53
00:03:30,121 --> 00:03:32,290
- Hey, you.
- How are you?

54
00:03:32,540 --> 00:03:33,916
Good. How are you?

55
00:03:34,166 --> 00:03:35,376
Good.

56
00:03:35,626 --> 00:03:38,754
- Hi, honey.
- Hi, Julie. Hi, Julie?

57
00:03:39,005 --> 00:03:41,382
Julie!

58
00:03:41,841 --> 00:03:42,675
How are you?

59
00:03:42,925 --> 00:03:44,302
Good.

60
00:03:44,552 --> 00:03:46,887
So everybody's here.

61
00:03:47,138 --> 00:03:50,266
Everybody's good.

62
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:52,163
Good and great and here.

63
00:03:54,192 --> 00:03:56,445
Were you gonna play something?

64
00:03:56,695 --> 00:04:00,282
- Well, actually...
- Play it!

65
00:04:00,824 --> 00:04:02,451
All right.

66
00:04:02,701 --> 00:04:06,955
- Julie, I didn't know you wore lenses.
- What?

67
00:04:07,748 --> 00:04:09,249
Okay. Hi.

68
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:13,629
Hello. Hi. Okay.

69
00:04:13,795 --> 00:04:16,798
This is a song about a love triangle...

70
00:04:17,049 --> 00:04:20,594
...between three people I made up.

71
00:04:22,971 --> 00:04:27,184
It's called
"Two of Them Kissed Last Night."

72
00:04:29,186 --> 00:04:32,856
<i>There was a girl
We'll call her Betty</i>

73
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:36,860
<i>And a guy
Let's call him Neil</i>

74
00:04:37,110 --> 00:04:40,906
<i>Now I can't stress
This point too strongly</i>

75
00:04:41,156 --> 00:04:44,910
<i>This story isn't real</i>

76
00:04:46,537 --> 00:04:51,250
<i>Now our Neil must decide
Who will be the girl that he casts aside</i>

77
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,710
<i>Will Betty be the one
Who he loves truly</i>

78
00:04:53,961 --> 00:04:58,841
<i>Or will it be the one
Who we'll call Loolie</i>

79
00:05:00,884 --> 00:05:03,220
<i>He must decide
He must decide</i>

80
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:08,350
<i>Even though I made him up
He must decide</i>

81
00:05:10,561 --> 00:05:13,355
Well, this is a nice résumé.

82
00:05:13,605 --> 00:05:15,816
Nice, nice, nice.

83
00:05:16,066 --> 00:05:18,819
<i>Muy impressivo.</i>

84
00:05:18,751 --> 00:05:20,184
Shame none of it's true.

85
00:05:22,221 --> 00:05:23,188
I'm kidding.

86
00:05:24,023 --> 00:05:27,192
No, it's all true. I'm just
a little nervous, that's all.

87
00:05:27,727 --> 00:05:29,490
I'm fine now.

88
00:05:29,569 --> 00:05:34,574
Mr. Rastatter, what does this
job entail? The ad wasn't clear.

89
00:05:34,824 --> 00:05:36,743
Macholate.

90
00:05:36,993 --> 00:05:38,286
- I'm sorry?
- Macholate.

91
00:05:38,536 --> 00:05:42,290
It's a synthetic chocolate substitute.

92
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,543
Go ahead, try a piece.

93
00:05:45,794 --> 00:05:48,797
We think Macholate is
even better than chocolate.

94
00:05:49,047 --> 00:05:51,591
All right.

95
00:05:59,307 --> 00:06:01,643
I love how it crumbles.

96
00:06:01,893 --> 00:06:05,647
- You see, chocolate doesn't do that.
- No, ma'am.

97
00:06:05,897 --> 00:06:10,318
We should be getting
our FDA approval any day now.

98
00:06:10,443 --> 00:06:12,904
Hopefully, in time for Thanksgiving.

99
00:06:13,154 --> 00:06:15,615
The way we see it,
chocolate dominates...

100
00:06:15,865 --> 00:06:20,662
...your major food-preparation holidays.
Easter, Christmas, what have you.

101
00:06:20,912 --> 00:06:22,956
But given the right marketing...

102
00:06:23,206 --> 00:06:27,252
...we can make Thanksgiving
the Macholate holiday.

103
00:06:27,335 --> 00:06:28,920
Wow.

104
00:06:29,170 --> 00:06:31,464
Aren't you gonna swallow that?

105
00:06:31,715 --> 00:06:34,134
Just waiting for it to stop bubbling.

106
00:06:34,384 --> 00:06:37,345
Isn't that great?

107
00:06:38,346 --> 00:06:39,639
Well, anyhow...

108
00:06:39,889 --> 00:06:43,351
...we're looking for chefs
who can create Thanksgiving recipes.

109
00:06:43,601 --> 00:06:44,769
You interested?

110
00:06:45,020 --> 00:06:47,063
Abso...

111
00:06:47,314 --> 00:06:49,941
...- lutely!

112
00:06:50,275 --> 00:06:53,820
I love creating recipes,
I love Thanksgiving, and now...

113
00:06:54,070 --> 00:06:55,196
...I love Macholate.

114
00:06:55,447 --> 00:06:56,489
Really?

115
00:06:56,740 --> 00:06:59,367
Especially that aftertaste.
I tell you...

116
00:06:59,618 --> 00:07:03,246
...that'll last you till Christmas.

117
00:07:06,291 --> 00:07:08,001
How about Macholate mousse?

118
00:07:08,251 --> 00:07:09,419
It's not...

119
00:07:09,669 --> 00:07:11,463
...very Thanksgiving-y.

120
00:07:11,713 --> 00:07:15,008
How about Pilgrim Macholate mousse?

121
00:07:15,258 --> 00:07:16,551
What makes it Pilgrim?

122
00:07:16,801 --> 00:07:20,138
We'll put buckles on it.

123
00:07:22,140 --> 00:07:23,308
Did Ross call?

124
00:07:23,558 --> 00:07:25,435
No, I'm sorry.

125
00:07:25,685 --> 00:07:27,771
Why didn't he call?

126
00:07:28,021 --> 00:07:29,606
He's gonna stay with Julie.

127
00:07:29,856 --> 00:07:31,983
He's gonna stay with her
and she'll be:

128
00:07:32,233 --> 00:07:34,486
"Hi, I'm Julie. Ross picked me."

129
00:07:34,736 --> 00:07:40,367
"We'll get married and have lots
of kids and dig up stuff together!"

130
00:07:40,450 --> 00:07:44,704
No offense, but that
sounds nothing like her.

131
00:07:46,081 --> 00:07:50,085
What am I gonna do?
This is like a complete nightmare!

132
00:07:50,335 --> 00:07:55,548
I know. This must be so hard.
"Oh, no! Two women love me!"

133
00:07:55,799 --> 00:07:59,010
"They're both gorgeous,
my wallet's too small for my 50s...

134
00:07:59,261 --> 00:08:02,931
...and my diamond shoes are too tight!"

135
00:08:03,181 --> 00:08:07,936
- Here's a thought...
- Don't ever touch the computer.

136
00:08:08,186 --> 00:08:10,981
Ross, listen.
I got two words for you:

137
00:08:11,231 --> 00:08:13,942
Threesome.

138
00:08:18,264 --> 00:08:20,559
You still have another
word if you wanna use it.

139
00:08:21,901 --> 00:08:25,359
Hey, I think I know what it is: help.

140
00:08:25,661 --> 00:08:28,372
Let's get logical about this.
We'll make a list.

141
00:08:28,622 --> 00:08:32,585
"Rachel and Julie: Pros and Cons."

142
00:08:35,254 --> 00:08:37,965
We'll put their names
in different fonts...

143
00:08:38,215 --> 00:08:40,843
...and I can use different
colors for each column.

144
00:08:41,093 --> 00:08:42,344
Can't we use a pen?

145
00:08:42,595 --> 00:08:45,973
No, Amish boy.

146
00:08:46,390 --> 00:08:50,060
Let's start with the cons
because they're more fun.

147
00:08:50,311 --> 00:08:51,896
Rachel first.

148
00:08:52,146 --> 00:08:53,606
I don't know.

149
00:08:53,856 --> 00:08:55,024
I mean...

150
00:08:55,274 --> 00:08:59,987
All right, I guess you can say
she's a little spoiled sometimes.

151
00:09:00,237 --> 00:09:03,490
You could say that.

152
00:09:03,782 --> 00:09:07,912
I guess, sometimes
she's a little ditzy, you know?

153
00:09:08,162 --> 00:09:11,499
And I've seen her be a little
too into her looks.

154
00:09:11,749 --> 00:09:13,834
And Julie and I have
a lot in common...

155
00:09:14,084 --> 00:09:16,962
...because we're both
paleontologists, right?

156
00:09:17,213 --> 00:09:19,006
But Rachel's just a waitress.

157
00:09:19,256 --> 00:09:20,966
Waitress.

158
00:09:21,217 --> 00:09:24,762
Got it.
You guys want to play Doom?

159
00:09:25,930 --> 00:09:29,558
Or we could keep doing this.

160
00:09:29,725 --> 00:09:31,352
What else?

161
00:09:31,602 --> 00:09:34,438
I don't know.

162
00:09:34,939 --> 00:09:39,026
Oh! Her ankles are a little chubby.

163
00:09:39,276 --> 00:09:40,694
Okay, let's do Julie.

164
00:09:40,945 --> 00:09:43,697
What's wrong with her?

165
00:09:45,908 --> 00:09:49,370
She's not Rachel.

166
00:09:49,881 --> 00:09:52,717
This is pumpkin pie
with a Macholate crust.

167
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:56,679
This is Macholate cranberry cake,
and these are Macholate-chip cookies.

168
00:09:56,929 --> 00:10:00,516
Just like the Indians served.

169
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:03,561
Oh, my God!

170
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:04,729
"Oh, my God" good?

171
00:10:04,979 --> 00:10:09,442
Oh, my God! I can't believe
you let me put this in my mouth.

172
00:10:09,692 --> 00:10:14,822
Sweet Lord!
This is what evil must taste like!

173
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:22,163
I tell you, it won't print.

174
00:10:22,413 --> 00:10:25,041
I pressed that button, like, 100 times.

175
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:28,795
For a hotline, you're not so hot.

176
00:10:29,671 --> 00:10:31,422
What is that in the background?

177
00:10:31,673 --> 00:10:34,634
Are you watching <i>Star Trek</i>?

178
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:44,310
So did you break Julie's heart?

179
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:50,316
It was horrible. She cried, I cried.
She threw things, they hit me.

180
00:10:51,693 --> 00:10:52,902
I did the right thing.

181
00:10:53,152 --> 00:10:57,282
So Spock actually hugs his father?

182
00:10:57,782 --> 00:11:00,994
Hey, do you guys have...

183
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:04,622
Where you going?

184
00:11:04,872 --> 00:11:08,209
I just got back...

185
00:11:08,459 --> 00:11:11,254
...from Julie's.

186
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:13,464
No, no.

187
00:11:13,715 --> 00:11:15,508
It's not what you think.

188
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:18,928
It's the other thing.

189
00:11:24,309 --> 00:11:29,022
Well, what's the other thing?
What do I think?

190
00:11:29,772 --> 00:11:30,982
Well...

191
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:33,943
He broke up with Julie!

192
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:38,364
Well, go hug her, for God's sakes!

193
00:11:38,615 --> 00:11:39,532
Really?

194
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:41,576
Really.

195
00:11:41,826 --> 00:11:43,703
It's always been you, Rach.

196
00:11:43,953 --> 00:11:47,165
Oh, God.

197
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:58,843
Oh, this is good.

198
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:01,179
- This is really good.
- I know. I know.

199
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:04,474
It's almost...

200
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:12,649
What do you say we take a walk?
Just us. Not them.

201
00:12:12,899 --> 00:12:16,110
- Let me get my coat.
- Okay. No, hey!

202
00:12:16,361 --> 00:12:19,322
I'll get your coat.

203
00:12:25,161 --> 00:12:28,540
He's going to get my coat.
He's going to get my coat, Joey!

204
00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:32,919
Joey, I can't believe this!
This is unbelievable!

205
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:37,131
- What's that?
- What? Nothing!

206
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:41,094
- I saw my name. What is it?
- No, no, see? See?

207
00:12:41,344 --> 00:12:43,346
It's printing!

208
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:46,015
It's printing!

209
00:12:46,516 --> 00:12:47,684
Let me see!

210
00:12:47,934 --> 00:12:49,561
Hey, someone order a coat?

211
00:12:49,811 --> 00:12:53,106
Chandler wrote something about me
and won't let me see.

212
00:12:53,356 --> 00:12:56,734
He won't? He won't!

213
00:12:57,151 --> 00:12:58,778
Because isn't that...

214
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:01,906
...the short story you were writing?

215
00:13:02,157 --> 00:13:04,367
Yes, it is a short story...

216
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:05,869
...that I was writing.

217
00:13:06,119 --> 00:13:07,996
And I'm in it?
Let me read it.

218
00:13:08,246 --> 00:13:10,748
No!

219
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:16,838
- Come on!
- Hey, why don't you read it to her?

220
00:13:25,471 --> 00:13:28,183
All right.

221
00:13:36,524 --> 00:13:39,402
"It was summer."

222
00:13:40,403 --> 00:13:42,572
"And it was hot."

223
00:13:42,822 --> 00:13:45,992
"Rachel was there."

224
00:13:47,869 --> 00:13:51,498
"A lonely gray couch."

225
00:13:52,207 --> 00:13:55,168
"'Oh, look!' cried Ned."

226
00:13:55,418 --> 00:13:59,380
"And the kingdom was his forever.
The end!"

227
00:14:01,508 --> 00:14:05,804
That's all you wrote?
You're the worst writer in the world!

228
00:14:06,054 --> 00:14:07,680
This isn't funny anymore.

229
00:14:07,931 --> 00:14:11,935
There's something about me
on that paper, and I want to see it.

230
00:14:12,185 --> 00:14:14,813
No, you don't.

231
00:14:15,772 --> 00:14:19,651
All right, fine. If you guys want
to be children, that's fine.

232
00:14:19,901 --> 00:14:23,071
I do not need to see it!

233
00:14:28,201 --> 00:14:29,202
What is this?

234
00:14:29,452 --> 00:14:32,288
That is...

235
00:14:32,372 --> 00:14:33,206
What is this?

236
00:14:33,456 --> 00:14:36,626
- Thank you.
- Good luck.

237
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:41,965
Okay. Just remember how crazy
I am about you, okay?

238
00:14:42,215 --> 00:14:44,008
"Kind of ditzy"?

239
00:14:44,259 --> 00:14:46,761
"Too into her looks"?

240
00:14:47,011 --> 00:14:48,012
"Spoiled"?

241
00:14:48,263 --> 00:14:53,309
A little spoiled. He was supposed
to type "little," the idiot!

242
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:56,187
"Just a waitress"?

243
00:14:56,438 --> 00:14:58,356
Now that was...

244
00:14:58,606 --> 00:15:01,985
I mean, as opposed to...

245
00:15:02,235 --> 00:15:05,113
Okay, is this over yet? Rach?

246
00:15:05,363 --> 00:15:08,700
I do not have chubby ankles!

247
00:15:08,950 --> 00:15:10,076
No! I...

248
00:15:10,326 --> 00:15:14,122
Okay, look at the other side.
Look at Julie's column.

249
00:15:14,372 --> 00:15:17,041
"She's not Rachem"?

250
00:15:17,292 --> 00:15:18,710
What the hell's a Rachem?

251
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:21,004
Is that a stupid paleontology word...

252
00:15:21,254 --> 00:15:23,923
...I wouldn't know,
because I'm just a waitress?

253
00:15:24,174 --> 00:15:27,218
Rach, come on!

254
00:15:27,886 --> 00:15:29,721
It's "She's not Rachel"!

255
00:15:29,971 --> 00:15:33,349
She's not...

256
00:15:39,731 --> 00:15:41,107
My diary! Brilliant!

257
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:45,153
If I'd said it was my diary,
she wouldn't have made me read it.

258
00:15:45,403 --> 00:15:51,201
That's true. You'd be a great person
to have around after an emergency.

259
00:15:51,451 --> 00:15:53,828
I cannot believe Ross
even made this list.

260
00:15:54,079 --> 00:15:57,457
- I know.
- What a dinkus!

261
00:15:57,707 --> 00:16:01,002
Hey, cut him some slack.
It was Chandler's idea.

262
00:16:01,252 --> 00:16:02,504
What?

263
00:16:02,754 --> 00:16:06,216
Oh, good. I was hoping
that would come up.

264
00:16:06,466 --> 00:16:07,801
This was your idea?

265
00:16:08,051 --> 00:16:12,472
Let's get some perspective here.
These things happen for a reason.

266
00:16:12,722 --> 00:16:15,558
Yeah. You!

267
00:16:15,809 --> 00:16:20,522
Pheebs, back me up. You believe
in that karma crap, don't you?

268
00:16:20,772 --> 00:16:25,652
By the way, good luck
in your next life as a dung beetle.

269
00:16:41,760 --> 00:16:44,304
Rach!

270
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:48,099
Hey! Open up! Please?

271
00:16:48,350 --> 00:16:52,270
When somebody does not buzz you in,
Ross, that means, "Go away."

272
00:16:52,521 --> 00:16:54,731
It doesn't mean,
"Climb up the fire escape."

273
00:16:54,981 --> 00:16:57,734
I just want to read you
your "Pro List."

274
00:16:57,984 --> 00:17:00,779
Not interested.

275
00:17:01,154 --> 00:17:04,616
"Number one:
The way you cry at game shows."

276
00:17:04,866 --> 00:17:08,411
"Number two:
How much you love your friends."

277
00:17:08,662 --> 00:17:12,666
"Number three: The way you play
with your hair when you're nervous."

278
00:17:12,916 --> 00:17:16,753
"Number four: How brave you are
for starting your life over."

279
00:17:17,003 --> 00:17:20,090
"Number five:
How great you are with Ben."

280
00:17:20,340 --> 00:17:24,511
"Number six: The way you smell."

281
00:17:25,262 --> 00:17:26,596
What are you doing?

282
00:17:26,847 --> 00:17:28,431
You want to open the window?

283
00:17:28,682 --> 00:17:31,101
Oh, yeah.

284
00:17:31,268 --> 00:17:33,645
- What are you doing out there?
- I'm...

285
00:17:33,895 --> 00:17:36,314
You must be freezing.
You know what you need?

286
00:17:36,565 --> 00:17:41,194
How about a nice, steaming
cup of hot Macholate?

287
00:17:43,905 --> 00:17:46,116
Come on, open up.

288
00:17:46,366 --> 00:17:49,453
Rach, come on.
You gotta give me another chance.

289
00:17:49,703 --> 00:17:51,371
No.

290
00:17:51,621 --> 00:17:53,665
- No?
- That's what I said.

291
00:17:53,915 --> 00:17:54,958
Maybe we should go.

292
00:17:55,208 --> 00:17:57,294
You don't have to go.
We're done.

293
00:17:57,544 --> 00:17:59,045
I know how you must...

294
00:17:59,296 --> 00:18:01,381
No! You don't, Ross.

295
00:18:01,631 --> 00:18:05,469
Imagine the worst things
you think about yourself.

296
00:18:05,719 --> 00:18:09,931
How would you feel if the person
you trusted most in the world...

297
00:18:10,182 --> 00:18:11,808
...not only thinks them too...

298
00:18:12,058 --> 00:18:16,021
...but actually uses them
as reasons not to be with you.

299
00:18:16,271 --> 00:18:21,318
No, but see, I want to be with you
in spite of all those things.

300
00:18:21,568 --> 00:18:24,196
Well, that's mighty big of you.

301
00:18:24,446 --> 00:18:26,865
I said, don't go!

302
00:18:29,159 --> 00:18:30,327
You know what?

303
00:18:30,577 --> 00:18:35,373
If it were the other way around, there
is nothing you could put on a list...

304
00:18:35,624 --> 00:18:38,794
...that would make me
not want to be with you.

305
00:18:39,044 --> 00:18:42,255
Well, then I guess that's
the difference between us.

306
00:18:42,506 --> 00:18:46,468
See, I'd never make a list.

307
00:19:00,649 --> 00:19:06,696
I never know how long to wait
in this situation before you can talk.

308
00:19:07,322 --> 00:19:10,242
Maybe a little longer.

309
00:19:14,287 --> 00:19:17,374
In these recipes,
the quantities may seem unusual.

310
00:19:17,624 --> 00:19:20,544
Like these coconut Macholate
holiday nut bars?

311
00:19:20,794 --> 00:19:23,880
I've indicated four cups of coconut
and four cups of nuts...

312
00:19:24,131 --> 00:19:28,301
...and only one tablespoon
of Macholate.

313
00:19:28,552 --> 00:19:30,804
Doesn't matter.

314
00:19:31,054 --> 00:19:33,557
Our FDA approval didn't come through.

315
00:19:33,807 --> 00:19:37,602
Something about laboratory rats.

316
00:19:37,853 --> 00:19:38,854
Gosh, I'm sorry.

317
00:19:39,104 --> 00:19:40,397
Yeah.

318
00:19:40,647 --> 00:19:43,567
Anyhow, here's your check.

319
00:19:43,817 --> 00:19:46,403
Thank you for all the trouble
you went through.

320
00:19:46,653 --> 00:19:50,657
Listen, you didn't eat a lot of it
while you were cooking, did you?

321
00:19:50,907 --> 00:19:52,367
Well, I ate some.

322
00:19:52,617 --> 00:19:56,455
Oh, some is fine.
Some is not a lot.

323
00:19:56,705 --> 00:20:01,209
So it doesn't burn
when you pee, does it?

324
00:20:17,601 --> 00:20:18,935
Is that him again?

325
00:20:19,186 --> 00:20:24,399
Tell him I'd come to the phone,
but my ankles are weighing me down.

326
00:20:25,525 --> 00:20:27,652
I don't think this is the best time.

327
00:20:27,903 --> 00:20:30,781
Look, can you do something for me?

328
00:20:31,031 --> 00:20:33,909
Sure. What?

329
00:20:36,370 --> 00:20:38,914
All right.

330
00:20:40,957 --> 00:20:42,501
Music?

331
00:20:42,751 --> 00:20:45,212
Sure.

332
00:20:50,884 --> 00:20:53,845
<i>The next one's dedicated
to Rachel from Ross.</i>

333
00:20:54,096 --> 00:20:56,932
<i>Rachel, he wants you to know
he's sorry for what he did...</i>

334
00:20:57,182 --> 00:21:00,102
<i>...and he hopes you can forgive him.</i>

335
00:21:00,352 --> 00:21:04,690
<i>See the stones set in your eyes</i>

336
00:21:04,940 --> 00:21:09,236
<i>See the thorn twist in your side</i>

337
00:21:09,486 --> 00:21:14,700
<i>I'll wait for you</i>

338
00:21:18,245 --> 00:21:21,999
<i>Sleight of hand and twist of fate</i>

339
00:21:22,249 --> 00:21:26,962
<i>On a bed of nails she makes me wait</i>

340
00:21:27,212 --> 00:21:31,550
<i>And I'll wait without you</i>

341
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:36,680
<i>We've just gotten a call from Rachel
and she told us what Ross did.</i>

342
00:21:36,930 --> 00:21:39,891
<i>It's pretty appalling.
And, Ross, if you're listening...</i>

343
00:21:40,142 --> 00:21:44,354
<i>...I don't want to play
your song anymore.</i>

344
00:21:48,525 --> 00:21:51,403
<i>Why don't we devote our time
to a couple that stands a chance?</i>

345
00:21:51,653 --> 00:21:54,031
<i>Avery, Michelle's sorry
she hit you with her car...</i>

346
00:21:54,281 --> 00:21:57,117
<i>...and she hopes you two
will work it out.</i>

347
00:21:57,367 --> 00:21:59,911
<i>There's a room where</i>

348
00:22:00,162 --> 00:22:03,540
<i>I can go</i>

349
00:22:03,790 --> 00:22:09,296
<i>And tell my secrets to</i>

350
00:22:09,546 --> 00:22:13,592
<i>In my room</i>

351
00:22:16,011 --> 00:22:20,182
<i>In my room</i>

352
00:22:31,151 --> 00:22:33,111
Thanks for coming in again.

353
00:22:33,362 --> 00:22:36,365
Not at all. I have no morals,
and I need the cash.

354
00:22:36,615 --> 00:22:39,451
It's like I'm looking in a mirror.

355
00:22:39,701 --> 00:22:43,622
Anyway, they're called Fish-tachios.

356
00:22:43,872 --> 00:22:46,500
They taste exactly
like pistachios...

357
00:22:46,750 --> 00:22:50,003
...but they're made
of reconstituted fish bits.

358
00:22:50,253 --> 00:22:52,631
Here, try one.

359
00:22:52,881 --> 00:22:55,676
- All right.
- You're not allergic to anything?

360
00:22:55,926 --> 00:22:56,718
Cat hair.

361
00:22:56,969 --> 00:22:59,930
Oh, sorry.
